<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-14T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/326: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-14T10:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            14, 1919, 10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 7.40 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>President inaugurated October 12th without incident. He held
                                reception 13th. No changes as yet in Cabinet except Minister of
                                Marine recently created by law.</p>
                            <p>No newspapers except sheet bulletin foreign news. Strikes apparently
                                ended owing to Government decree issued Saturday compelling
                                arbitration.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>